ExtraInfo.Rem: Nyquist was written by Roger B. Dannenberg and was intended to be used as a complete programming language for audio synthesis and analysis, with support for MIDI, audio recording and playback, file I/O, object-oriented programming, profiling, debugging, and more. Audacity uses only a subset of Nyquist's functionality, allowing you to take simple Nyquist functions and use them to process audio data.
